Sent from my Kindle Fire From: Jacqueline Crook <jcrook@mbopartners.com <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&mailto:jcrook@mbopartners.com?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D&mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D>> Sent: Thu Oct 25 16:28:35 EDT 2012 To: "ldaniel102@aol.com <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&mailto:ldaniel102@aol.com?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D&mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D>" <ldaniel102@aol.com <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&mailto:ldaniel102@aol.com?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D&mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D>> Subject: Net Cash Estimate Hi Larry, It was a pleasure speaking with you today! Thank you for your interest in MBO Partners. Briefly, and to review, MBO Partners is a service designed to provide its contractors with the back-office support, tax advantages, and freedoms of being an Independent Consultant with all the safety and benefits of a W-2 employer. To review, once you begin working as a contractor at EOIR Technologies, we'll engage you as a W-2 employee in our MBO Exec program. Then, as you work, we'll bill EOIR Technologies, collect your billings, withhold taxes, and reimburse your business expenses. We even cover you under our General and Professional Liability insurance at no cost to you. Plus, using MBO Partners couldn't be easier: you submit your expenses through your personal online MBO "Business Center" as you work and we will process your invoices, collect your invoice payments from your client, and process payroll for you. As discussed, here is some useful information about MBO: MBO Exec: General Information - An overview <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/Welcome_to_MBO_Partners.pdf?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> of the service - An interactive tool <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://www.mbopartners.com/?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D#whoweare> showing various aspects of MBO Exec - How MBO Exec compares <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Exec_vs_1099_Comparison.pdf?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> to working on a 1099 basis Operational information about the MBO Exec service - Our Business Expense Reimbursement Policy <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Partners_Expense_Policy.pdf?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> - A list of non-billable business expenses you may submit <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Partners_Expense_List.pdf?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> for pre-tax reimbursement - A list of some of the non-billable out of pocket medical expenses you can submit <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Partners_Medical_Expense_Eligibility_2011.pdf?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> for pre-tax reimbursement - Information about our 401K <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://info.mbopartners.com/rs/mbo/images/MBO_Partners_Associate_Retirement_Plan_Summary.pdf?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D>. Net Cash Estimate we discussed:Based on the bill rate of $200 per hour at about 20 hours per month, I have created a Net Cash Estimate to give you an idea of how the cash flow will run through MBO. Per the attached document, please review as follows: The estimate will be broken down into three columns: the first being prior to FUTA and SUTA tax caps being met ($56.00/year for FUTA and $942.00/year for SUTA in OH as listed in the "Business Center Payroll Tax Breakdown" box on the right), the second column is in later months after those tax caps are hit, and the last column is on an annualized basis. The first section is detailing the billing to Booz Allen. We estimated $4,000 a month. The Total Income/Receipts is the payment we can expect to see from Eoir Technologies. The next section, Use of Business Center Funds, is detailing all of the pre-tax deductions. Our service fee is coming out pre-tax as well as one half of the equivalent of self-employment tax (SS and Medicare) + FUTA and SUTA. Again, the breakdown of the Business Center Payroll Tax Breakdown is in the box on the right. Your Gross W2 Pay is your taxable figure. The items that are withheld post-tax are the other half of self-employment tax (SS and Medicare) as well as your standard federal and state withholdings. Your Net Pay is your take home. Please take note of your total cash. Please let me know if you have any questions on the estimates; I'd be happy to explain further. I appreciate you taking the time for our call today and I look forward to working with you further! Jackie___________________________________Jacqueline CrookClient Enrollment ManagerMBO Partners t: 703.793.6280f: 703.793.6454e: jcrook@mbopartners.com <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&jcrook@mbopartners.com?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D&mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D>w: www.mbopartners.com <http://mkto-l0128.com/track?t=c&&&&http://www.mbopartners.com/?mkt_tok=2xUAKZjCV3VYu05z563JcInskDmOeZel0dYXY52MuKVUsyIUGIalUg%3D%3D> </html
